1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,080
Dad!

2
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,480
<i>Wad and his gang</i>

3
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:09,120
<i>robbed and slaughtered</i>
<i>the family of Khun Yod Pakdee.</i>

4
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,120
I raised you. I believe

5
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,840
you weren't born rotten, Lasor.

6
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:24,800
I just hope Lasor finally opens his eyes

7
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,680
and sees Petch's true nature
for what it is.

8
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,720
- Yiwha.
- Yiwha.

9
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,600
Yiwha!

10
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,200
<i>Those two share the same heart.</i>

11
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,760
We need to find a cure
before the heart stops completely.

12
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:46,000
You need the pollen of the Twin Lotus.

13
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,760
Twin Lotus pollen?

14
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,720
If we save Yiwha,

15
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,560
Lasor will wake up too, right?

16
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:59,440
Yiwha and Lasor share the same heart.

17
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:01,480
If one dies, the other dies.

18
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,000
If one survives, the other survives.

19
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:07,680
Then no matter how despicable Lasor is,

20
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,120
I can't do anything to him at all.

21
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:15,120
That's why I tried to cleanse
the dark sorcery from his body,

22
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,440
erase all his memories,

23
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:20,320
and send him somewhere no one knows him.

24
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,680
That's no different

25
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:26,000
from helping him
escape the crimes he's committed.

26
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:32,160
Or would you rather see
Yiwha meet the same end as Lasor?

27
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,160
What's that?

28
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,360
A Tabong Plam,

29
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:49,200
a giant forest centipede.
Its venom can kill an elephant.

30
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,360
"Tabong Plam, mighty and grand,

31
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:56,600
deep in the jungle, red as fire…"

32
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,800
I've only heard the name.

33
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,600
I thought it existed only in legends.

34
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,960
There's a lot more you need to learn.

35
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,400
Sometimes, what you think you know

36
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:12,040
isn't the whole truth.

37
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,960
Phraya Kaipetch, that corrupt governor,

38
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:40,560
signed agreements with foreign traders

39
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,920
to open brothels, gambling dens,

40
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,600
and opium houses

41
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,120
right here in Tha Khiri.

42
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,880
Will we accept this?

43
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,240
No!

44
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:58,280
They'll turn Tha Khiri

45
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,960
into a den of vice,
drugging and corrupting our people.

46
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,360
How are our children
supposed to live like this?

47
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,720
That's right!

48
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:12,760
All of this is because Phraya Kaipetch

49
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:16,160
exploits the people, sells out our land,

50
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,840
and bleeds us dry

51
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,600
until we're nearly starving.

52
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,920
- Isn't that true?
- True!

53
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:27,080
How many lives have already been
sacrificed to his hunger for power?

54
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,640
It's time

55
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:33,160
we stop bowing our heads
to wicked men like him!

56
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,400
Let us unite and fight

57
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,920
for justice.

58
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,560
Drive Phraya Kaipetch

59
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,720
out of our city!

60
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,240
Phraya Kaipetch, get out!

61
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:49,400
- Get out!
- Get out!

62
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:52,200
- Get out!
- Get out!

63
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,760
- Get out!
- Hey! You rebels!

64
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,880
- Arrest them!
- Everyone.

65
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,760
Let's run!

66
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,000
Chang, go.

67
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,440
- Stop!
- Chang!

68
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,400
- Talong!
- Talong, run!

69
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,400
- Chang!
- Talong!

70
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,480
- Talong! Talong!
- I'm going to help Chang!

71
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:28,360
Even if you go back now,
you won't be able to help him.

72
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,960
It's better than doing nothing!

73
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:35,680
If you really want to help Chang,
you need to start using your head.

74
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:49,800
Do you know where the police took him?

75
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,480
So, will you talk now?

76
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,800
Where are your rebel friends hiding?

77
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:06,360
I won't tell you.

78
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,800
I really want to see

79
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,200
how much longer you can last.

80
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,360
Hey, Blur.

81
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:06,160
There's plenty of space.
Why are you crowding me?

82
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,520
I'm cold.

83
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,720
Let me squeeze in a bit.

84
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,120
Back in the cave, when we found the iron,

85
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,400
we were closer than this.

86
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,680
Why would you say that?

87
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,200
You're making me shy.

88
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:38,960
We're already husband and wife.
What's there to be shy about?

89
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,520
Who said

90
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,800
I was your wife?

91
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,000
We're not married yet.

92
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,200
Orror,

93
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:58,680
when we get back, I'll ask your father

94
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,040
for your hand.

95
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,760
But my father is fierce,

96
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,160
fierce like a tiger.

97
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:10,160
Aren't you scared?

98
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,240
I am.

99
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,920
I'm scared of not having you as my wife.

100
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:28,920
Orror.

101
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,160
The night Yod died…

102
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:53,400
if my Chum Suea camp
hadn't been raided by Duang's men first,

103
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:55,840
I would've taken your family and Yiwha

104
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,920
safely to Nakhon.

105
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,320
What are you talking about?

106
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,840
Yod and I

107
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:09,640
were sworn brothers.

108
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,600
We even promised each other

109
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:16,720
that if one of us had a son
and the other had a daughter,

110
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,720
when they grew up,

111
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,200
we'd have them marry.

112
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:32,200
Everything would've ended well…

113
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,840
if Yod hadn't met his fate first.

114
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,040
I don't believe in fate.

115
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:52,120
I believe in karma.

116
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:01,600
I won't make excuses.

117
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:05,160
Lasor is truly guilty.

118
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:10,120
But right now,

119
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:14,200
working together to eliminate Petch
is more important.

120
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:19,000
I want you to join me.

121
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:22,720
Why should I help you?

122
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:25,800
So our homeland
doesn't get ruined even more than this.

123
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,960
Once Kaipetch is gone,

124
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:32,000
then we can settle what's between us.

125
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:50,400
<i>Do not let the candle go out.</i>
<i>Those wandering spirits are waiting</i>

126
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,880
<i>for a chance to possess my daughter.</i>

127
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,600
<i>- I want it.</i>
<i>- I want her body.</i>

128
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:22,960
<i>- I want her body.</i>
<i>- I want it.</i>

129
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:26,840
<i>- I want her body.</i>
<i>- I want it.</i>

130
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:30,640
<i>- I want it.</i>
<i>- I want her body.</i>

131
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,960
<i>- I want her body.</i>
<i>- I want it.</i>

132
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:37,440
<i>- I want her body.</i>
<i>- I want it.</i>

133
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:42,520
<i>- I want it.</i>
<i>- I want her body.</i>

134
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:32,440
- Help!
- Lady Duen.

135
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,840
Ghosts! There are ghosts outside!

136
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:40,920
Lady Duen, shut the window tight.

137
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,560
Watch the candle. Don't let it go out.

138
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:33,800
Yiam.

139
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:47,200
May I sleep with you?

140
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,400
You're not Yiwha.

141
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:54,120
Leave, you hollow-backed ghost.

142
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,520
I don't want to hurt you. Go!

143
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,880
She's getting away.

144
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,800
Let her go.

145
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,320
She just wanted
to warm herself by the fire.

146
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,640
We go our separate ways.

147
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:15,680
Don't harm each other.

148
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,960
I'll pray and dedicate merit to you.

149
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,200
Chang.

150
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,960
Chang.

151
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:52,880
Chang.

152
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,720
We're here to get you out.

153
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:13,840
Are you hurt?

154
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:21,240
- Slowly, Chang.
- Slowly.

155
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:22,920
- Chang.
- Slowly.

156
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:31,520
Right on time, Pun.

157
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:33,240
Don't!

158
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:35,280
Why did you shoot my friend?!

159
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:37,320
Orders from Phraya Kaipetch.

160
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,400
See a rebel, shoot on sight.

161
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,440
- Talong!
- Talong!

162
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,040
Talong.

163
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:06,880
Talong.

164
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:11,800
Talong.

165
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,599
Talong.

166
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,079
Talong…

167
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:22,960
Talong…

168
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:29,280
Pun, please help Talong.

169
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:33,520
Pun.

170
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,360
Take Chang and run.

171
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:40,280
Don't worry about me.

172
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:46,360
I'm not leaving.

173
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,400
You're coming with me, Talong.

174
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,960
Prison break!

175
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,800
Chang. Chang…

176
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:58,720
Chang. Chang! We need to go.

177
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,560
We need to run now. Chang, come on!

178
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,480
- Talong…
- Chang!

179
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:06,240
Talong!

180
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:02,440
I'm the one who should've died,

181
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:05,200
not Talong.

182
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:08,600
Talong must've loved you so much,

183
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:12,800
enough to die for you.

184
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,720
Those bastards.

185
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:19,960
I'll kill them all.

186
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:22,880
We'll never be able to kill them all

187
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:27,360
as long as Phraya Kaipetch is still alive.

188
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:41,240
I'll kill Kaipetch.

189
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,560
I'll avenge Talong.

190
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,320
You have to help me, Pun.

191
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:12,480
I've never climbed Khao Phrom
this high before.

192
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:15,240
The top of Khao Phrom is sacred ground.

193
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:20,120
If you don't have the merit for it,
don't expect to reach the top.

194
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:25,800
This place once served
as a retreat for hermits

195
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:29,720
and enlightened monks
with great spiritual power.

196
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,880
I, Bandit Wad,

197
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:45,520
never once intended to harm Yod,

198
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:48,640
my fellow disciple.

199
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:51,320
Let Heaven and Earth,

200
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:55,160
and all sacred spirits here,

201
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:57,480
bear witness to my innocence.

202
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,440
And may the truth

203
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,480
be revealed soon.

204
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,120
That's the lotus pond.

205
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,640
<i>Jindamanee piyan mantang,</i>

206
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:41,160
<i>yasangtha sangkomang upasanti</i>

207
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:43,640
<i>sinehang matapitava</i>

208
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:47,080
<i>orasang paphotanja maharaja…</i>

209
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:31,640
Yiwha.

210
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:36,480
Your medicine worked.

211
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:40,520
Dad…

212
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:43,440
Yiwha.

213
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,600
You're safe now.

214
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,280
Yiam.

215
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:14,760
Yiwha.

216
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,160
I'm sorry.

217
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,240
I won't ever do that again.

218
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,680
Please don't leave me.

219
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,240
If you love me this much,

220
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:38,880
how could I ever leave you?

221
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,120
Lasor.

222
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,560
You're awake.

223
00:24:48,240 --> 00:24:49,800
I was so worried.

224
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,960
Lasor doesn't die that easily.

225
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:17,360
Lasor,

226
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:21,760
last night the ghosts tried to break in.

227
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:24,000
There were so many.

228
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:27,080
And I just found out

229
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,040
that Nui is a ghost too.

230
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:37,120
I saw ghosts fighting ghosts.

231
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,960
I was scared to death.

232
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:43,480
My lady.

233
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:49,120
Nui is a ghost I keep.

234
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:50,960
Don't be afraid.

235
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:53,160
He won't hurt you.

236
00:25:57,400 --> 00:26:00,200
If I stay around ghosts long enough,
I'll probably get used to it.

237
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,920
Come here.

238
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:38,960
Nui.

239
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,240
I was almost killed by Yiam's spell.

240
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:43,320
Who saved me?

241
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:48,160
The ones who saved you
were Father Wad and Yiam.

242
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:54,680
That day Yiam
used the heart-twisting spell on you,

243
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:56,680
Yiwha was affected too

244
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:59,640
because you're twins.

245
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:29,920
Lasor.

246
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:32,640
- Lasor.
- Yiam.

247
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:34,200
Please.

248
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:12,960
I'm sorry.

249
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,800
Bandit Pud

250
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:58,200
used the Narai transformation spell
to impersonate you.

251
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:01,960
He bewitched me,

252
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,280
forced me to kill Khun Yod,

253
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,360
to take revenge

254
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:18,080
because Khun Yod
once tried to get rid of him.

255
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:20,720
My mother and my sister

256
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:22,040
didn't know anything,

257
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:25,640
but they still died
because of you and Bandit Pud.

258
00:29:26,360 --> 00:29:27,600
I made a mistake.

259
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:32,240
I know my apology

260
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,720
can't erase what I did that night.

261
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:44,520
I was lost, intoxicated by dark sorcery

262
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:46,800
and it got Nui killed.

263
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,440
Dad, I wronged you again and again…

264
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:59,120
until I couldn't even look you in the eye.

265
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,920
Even if the law can't touch me,

266
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:08,280
karma is punishing me.

267
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:10,360
I can't live in peace anymore.

268
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:16,680
Dad,

269
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:21,240
I want to be free of this
once and for all.

270
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:32,360
We can't turn back time and fix the past.

271
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:35,480
But it's not too late to change now.

272
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:43,000
It's too late, Yiwha.

273
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:46,200
A filthy bastard like me

274
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,160
doesn't deserve forgiveness.

275
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,720
I only feel sorry for you.

276
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:59,440
You have to carry
the consequences in my place.

277
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:05,600
Lasor.

278
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,560
Do you remember what I once asked of you?

279
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:13,920
I'm going to cleanse
the dark sorcery from you

280
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,800
and erase all your memories.

281
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:19,000
Will you accept it?

282
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:24,200
Yes.

283
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:27,680
I'll do anything

284
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:31,120
as long as Yiwha is safe.

285
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:38,320
Thank you, Lasor.

286
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:59,040
I know you're not happy.

287
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,960
And what can I do?

288
00:32:07,320 --> 00:32:09,200
If I hand Lasor over to the Patrol Unit,

289
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,680
he'll be beheaded,

290
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:13,680
and you'll die with him.

291
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,080
But if I let him go,

292
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:18,840
I'll feel like I've betrayed my family.

293
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,600
If you're going to
turn him over to the Patrol Unit,

294
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:25,440
then I'm willing to accept
the death penalty alongside Lasor.

295
00:32:26,080 --> 00:32:27,440
This has nothing to do with you.

296
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:29,840
It does.

297
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,800
We're siblings.

298
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:36,680
If my brother sins,
I bear the consequences too.

299
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:40,440
But no matter what you choose,

300
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:42,880
I'll accept it.

301
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:48,600
Why aren't you taking
your brother's side like you always do?

302
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:52,800
Because my brother truly did wrong.

303
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,760
He confessed to everything,

304
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:58,680
and he's remorseful now.

305
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,960
So you want me to forgive him?

306
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:07,080
To let him off the hook?

307
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,160
That's up to you.

308
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:13,960
But have you ever thought about this?

309
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:16,640
If you get your revenge,

310
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:18,800
what will you gain?

311
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:22,680
Will you really be happy?

312
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:44,200
After your memory is erased,
I'll have you ordained

313
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:47,600
and send you to Lanka.

314
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:50,000
The saffron robe will protect you,

315
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,320
so no one can lay a hand on you again.

316
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,160
And you, Nui,

317
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:02,320
once everything is done,

318
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,520
I'll send you on to your next life.

319
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:07,720
So you won't have to wander,
following your master like this.

320
00:34:12,239 --> 00:34:13,320
Yes, Father Wad.

321
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:19,760
When will you cleanse
the dark sorcery from Lasor?

322
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:21,239
In three days.

323
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:25,400
It's an auspicious time to lift the curse.

324
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:27,320
Dad.

325
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:29,840
Before I go,

326
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:34,199
may I say goodbye to someone
for the last time?

327
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:04,040
What's wrong with you?
Is something going on?

328
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,960
I came to say goodbye.

329
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:21,200
Goodbye?

330
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:24,200
Where are you going, Lasor?

331
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,800
Somewhere so far…

332
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,680
that no one will remember me.

333
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,360
Take me with you.

334
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:40,880
No matter how far,
no matter how hard, I won't complain.

335
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:42,840
I just want to be with you.

336
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:07,440
You can't, my lady.

337
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:12,520
I'll have someone
escort you to Phra Nakhon.

338
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,640
And after that,

339
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:19,680
you must forget everything
that ever happened here.

340
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,800
You want me to forget you too?

341
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:41,560
In the end, everyone leaves me,

342
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:43,880
even you.

343
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:39,800
The railway has been destroyed,
smashed to pieces.

344
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:42,560
What do you have to say,

345
00:37:43,920 --> 00:37:45,160
Phraya Kaipetch?

346
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:49,040
It was all the work of those rebels,

347
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:52,320
trying to strip me
of my position as governor, sir.

348
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:54,760
But what I've heard

349
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:57,200
is that you teamed up

350
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:59,720
with those hook-nosed foreigners,

351
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:02,360
Chinese triads,

352
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:05,280
and all kinds
of strange-tongued outsiders,

353
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,920
building the railway

354
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:09,880
so you could open brothels,
illegal gambling dens,

355
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:11,680
and opium houses,

356
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:15,000
selling out your land and your country,

357
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,400
until the masked rebel uprising

358
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:22,440
rose to oppose you. Isn't that the truth?

359
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,280
No, sir.

360
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:28,920
I'm being framed.
Who would dare do such a thing?

361
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:33,120
If there's no fire, there's no smoke.

362
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:35,120
It's disappointing.

363
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:38,400
I sent you to govern Tha Khiri

364
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:41,760
hoping you'd relieve the people's
suffering and bring them wellbeing,

365
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:44,760
to develop the city

366
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:48,560
in line with His Majesty's wishes.

367
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:54,920
But you've only thrown the southern cities

368
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:57,240
into deeper chaos.

369
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:59,040
Is that acceptable?

370
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:02,880
I've served beneath the royal feet

371
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:06,960
with unwavering loyalty.

372
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:11,640
But those rebels spread rumors,
incited the villagers,

373
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:14,720
and defied royal authority.

374
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:19,440
Please, Your Excellency, grant me justice.

375
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:27,760
You say one thing.

376
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:33,600
But I hear another.

377
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:36,320
You traitorous governor.

378
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:37,920
How much more
are you going to rob this town?

379
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,760
We're starving to death. Do you even know?

380
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:44,320
Scum like you only weighs down the land.
Get out!

381
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:45,760
Wait, wait.

382
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:48,840
What's going on?

383
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,480
You still have the nerve to ask?

384
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:52,400
Hey.

385
00:39:58,240 --> 00:39:59,440
Open your eyes and look.

386
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:03,040
The proof is right there.
What excuse do you have now.

387
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,200
You bastard. Get out!

388
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:08,640
- Get out!
- Go!

389
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:10,760
- Get out!
- Get out!

390
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:14,640
- Get out!
- Get out!

391
00:40:14,720 --> 00:40:16,720
- Get out!
- Get out!

392
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:18,360
- You bastard.
- Don't ever come back.

393
00:40:26,640 --> 00:40:27,640
I suppose

394
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:31,240
I'll have to go down to Tha Khiri

395
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,200
and see it with my own eyes.

396
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:51,640
Uncle Niem is really dead?

397
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:59,880
Niem chose to die in my place.

398
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:03,480
That's why Uncle Chaem and I survived.

399
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:09,680
Petch could even kill a fellow disciple.

400
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,680
I have a bad feeling

401
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:18,840
he was behind Yod's death.

402
00:41:25,640 --> 00:41:27,360
But back then,
Duang was the governor of Tha Khiri,

403
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,000
not Phraya Kaipetch.

404
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:36,040
Yiam,

405
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,240
do you remember

406
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:41,240
what Duang said before he died?

407
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:45,600
There was an order…

408
00:41:45,680 --> 00:41:48,280
I was ordered to kill Khun Yod Pakdee.

409
00:41:49,880 --> 00:41:51,000
By whom?

410
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,320
Phraya…

411
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:09,440
Maybe the one
who ordered Duang to kill Khun Yod

412
00:42:09,520 --> 00:42:11,400
was Phraya Kaipetch.

413
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:17,920
Petch. It has to be him.

414
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:24,160
Now we share the same enemy.

415
00:42:25,520 --> 00:42:27,560
We have to deal with Phraya Kaipetch

416
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:30,920
before he does anything worse.

417
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:43,600
I'll work with you

418
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:46,680
to wipe out that villain,

419
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:49,400
the thorn in this land.

420
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:53,440
Everything else, we'll deal with later.

421
00:43:39,160 --> 00:43:40,560
Are you thinking about Uncle Niem?

422
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:48,320
Why does my family

423
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:52,560
have to go through something like this?

424
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:01,160
You still have your dad

425
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:04,040
and your brother, Yiwha.

426
00:44:04,640 --> 00:44:06,120
But in just three days,

427
00:44:07,280 --> 00:44:11,160
Lasor won't be the same person anymore.

428
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:14,040
He's only having his memories erased.

429
00:44:15,280 --> 00:44:17,040
He's not being killed.

430
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:19,400
Why are you so sad?

431
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:22,880
Losing your memories

432
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:26,720
is like dying while still being alive.

433
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:30,800
And he'll have to
wander off somewhere else.

434
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:34,120
I can't help worrying about Lasor.

435
00:44:45,480 --> 00:44:46,600
If it were the old me,

436
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:51,440
I wouldn't have let him go so easily.

437
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:56,160
I'd fight until one of us died.

438
00:44:58,480 --> 00:45:00,720
Then why did you change your mind?

439
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:10,680
Because the love I have for you

440
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:15,720
is above all my hatred.

441
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:22,760
You're that afraid I'll die?

442
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,040
What's the point of me living

443
00:45:29,600 --> 00:45:30,720
if I don't have you?

444
00:45:38,840 --> 00:45:40,080
And if I don't have you,

445
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:43,200
I can't live either.

446
00:46:13,080 --> 00:46:15,160
Those rebels stirred up the townspeople

447
00:46:15,240 --> 00:46:18,200
and used the documents
you signed with foreign traders

448
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:20,000
to expose you at the market, sir.

449
00:46:20,920 --> 00:46:23,040
Who dares poke the bear?

450
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:26,240
Pun, Chang, and Talong, sir.

451
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:30,880
Go find them.

452
00:46:30,960 --> 00:46:32,520
Bring them to me.

453
00:46:33,400 --> 00:46:34,760
- Go.
- Yes, sir.

454
00:46:34,840 --> 00:46:37,600
Hey, wait. Where is Lasor?

455
00:46:56,880 --> 00:46:58,320
Lasor,

456
00:46:58,400 --> 00:47:01,680
if you wipe out Yiam and his gang,

457
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:07,200
I'll appoint you chief tax collector

458
00:47:07,280 --> 00:47:09,520
of all Tha Khiri,

459
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:11,880
replacing that tycoon Thongyoo.

460
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:16,240
Master Kaipetch,

461
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:19,480
why did you kill my father?

462
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:22,520
Why did you kill Uncle Niem?

463
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:28,520
They were criminal scum.

464
00:47:29,920 --> 00:47:31,000
Why keep them alive?

465
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:33,520
If you let them live,

466
00:47:34,160 --> 00:47:37,360
they'll only make the villagers suffer.

467
00:47:37,440 --> 00:47:39,040
Don't you get it?

468
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:40,880
But that was my father.

469
00:47:42,520 --> 00:47:44,120
He was my benefactor.

470
00:47:46,280 --> 00:47:47,320
And what about me?

471
00:47:48,080 --> 00:47:49,760
Haven't I done anything for you at all?

472
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:52,960
How many times have I saved you?

473
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:55,560
You don't remember, Lasor?

474
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:57,080
You saved me

475
00:47:58,080 --> 00:47:59,880
because you wanted revenge on my father.

476
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:04,240
Remember this.

477
00:48:05,200 --> 00:48:06,400
From now on,

478
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:08,440
I

479
00:48:09,680 --> 00:48:12,200
won't be a pawn
in your revenge ever again.

480
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:31,320
You'll regret this, Lasor.

481
00:48:34,720 --> 00:48:36,440
THE GOVERNOR OF THA KHIRI GRANTS
PERMISSION TO DAMONT, NOËL, AND HENRI

482
00:48:36,520 --> 00:48:38,160
TO FREELY ESTABLISH OPIUM DENS,
GAMBLING HOUSES, AND BROTHELS.

483
00:48:41,600 --> 00:48:44,120
Kaipetch! Traitorous thief!

484
00:48:44,720 --> 00:48:48,160
The townspeople
have risen up against Phraya Kaipetch.

485
00:48:48,960 --> 00:48:53,440
If we let this continue,
it may spiral into civil war, sir.

486
00:48:55,720 --> 00:48:58,720
Go on. Prepare my travel procession.

487
00:48:59,400 --> 00:49:01,440
I'm going down to Tha Khiri immediately.

488
00:49:05,480 --> 00:49:06,360
Yes, sir.

489
00:49:24,720 --> 00:49:25,680
Your Excellency.

490
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:28,720
Talong is dead, sir.

491
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:31,320
Good. That's one less enemy.

492
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:34,320
But the police informant working for us
is dead too, sir.

493
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:38,560
Your Excellency.

494
00:49:38,640 --> 00:49:39,800
What now?

495
00:49:39,880 --> 00:49:42,040
An informant from the capital reports that

496
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:44,840
Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet
is on his way to Tha Khiri, sir.

497
00:49:49,160 --> 00:49:51,040
I can't let the people from the palace

498
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:53,080
see this chaos right now.

499
00:49:55,160 --> 00:49:58,120
Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet
is the High Commissioner,

500
00:49:58,200 --> 00:50:00,000
acting as His Majesty's eyes and ears.

501
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:02,080
Who would dare stand in his way, sir?

502
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:05,480
Have our men

503
00:50:05,560 --> 00:50:09,400
disguise themselves as masked rebels
and block the procession.

504
00:50:10,160 --> 00:50:14,280
Then spread the word
that it was Yiam and his gang.

505
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:17,280
And if you get the chance,

506
00:50:18,520 --> 00:50:19,960
kill him.

507
00:50:21,880 --> 00:50:22,960
Go!

508
00:50:34,320 --> 00:50:35,760
My lady. My lady.

509
00:50:37,560 --> 00:50:39,800
- It's me.
- Lasor.

510
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:42,880
What happened?

511
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:45,040
Lasor,

512
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:46,800
I have something important to tell you.

513
00:50:51,520 --> 00:50:54,760
Lady Duen overheard that Phraya Kaipetch
is planning something huge,

514
00:50:54,840 --> 00:50:56,640
to assassinate Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet,

515
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:59,040
the High Commissioner from the capital.

516
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:03,760
Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet
may be blunt and loud,

517
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:06,520
but he's an honest, upright official.

518
00:51:06,600 --> 00:51:10,840
I don't want him to die at the hands
of someone as vile as Phraya Kaipetch.

519
00:51:11,960 --> 00:51:13,120
A filthy plan,

520
00:51:14,360 --> 00:51:16,760
using men disguised as me

521
00:51:16,840 --> 00:51:18,320
to assassinate the High Commissioner.

522
00:51:19,360 --> 00:51:20,320
Disgusting.

523
00:51:24,880 --> 00:51:26,360
We have to protect

524
00:51:26,440 --> 00:51:29,800
the High Commissioner
and get him safely to Tha Khiri,

525
00:51:29,880 --> 00:51:32,960
so he can see Kaipetch's rot for himself

526
00:51:33,640 --> 00:51:36,400
and bring him to justice
for everything he's done.

527
00:51:38,920 --> 00:51:40,240
When will they strike?

528
00:51:41,280 --> 00:51:42,840
Do you know, my lady?

529
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:44,160
Tomorrow.

530
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:48,360
They'll lie in wait to assassinate him

531
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:50,920
at the forest edge
outside Tha Khiri's city gate.

532
00:51:51,680 --> 00:51:53,080
They won't succeed.

533
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:55,600
I'll protect the High Commissioner myself.

534
00:51:55,680 --> 00:51:56,800
I'm coming too.

535
00:51:57,320 --> 00:51:58,480
No, you're not.

536
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:20,040
You can come if you want.

537
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:24,720
But don't get in my way.

538
00:52:30,720 --> 00:52:31,560
Dad.

539
00:52:33,160 --> 00:52:34,560
I have something to ask.

540
00:52:49,600 --> 00:52:50,720
Don't worry, my lady.

541
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:55,480
Uncle Chaem has found someone trustworthy
to escort you to the capital.

542
00:52:56,320 --> 00:52:58,600
I guarantee you'll be safe.

543
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:08,160
Can't you let me stay with you?

544
00:53:14,800 --> 00:53:18,200
No, my lady. It's too dangerous.

545
00:53:19,320 --> 00:53:22,400
You shouldn't gamble your life
on someone who is cornered like me.

546
00:53:24,520 --> 00:53:28,400
I did wrong, and I have to pay for it.

547
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:32,560
Once I've sent you back to the capital,

548
00:53:33,400 --> 00:53:34,640
I'll have no worries left.

549
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,040
After that,

550
00:53:38,160 --> 00:53:39,400
I intend to ordain

551
00:53:40,120 --> 00:53:42,880
and serve the Buddha's teachings
for the rest of my life.

552
00:54:16,280 --> 00:54:17,480
Go now, my lady,

553
00:54:19,480 --> 00:54:21,080
before it gets dark.

554
00:54:57,760 --> 00:54:58,920
In the end,

555
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:03,200
you and I truly live in different worlds.

556
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:11,320
Soon enough,

557
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:14,200
Tha Khiri

558
00:55:14,880 --> 00:55:16,240
will become a city of sin.

559
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:19,440
People are starving

560
00:55:19,520 --> 00:55:22,320
because Phraya Kaipetch
squeezes us dry with extortionate taxes.

561
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:25,120
How many bodies
have already been sacrificed

562
00:55:25,800 --> 00:55:28,080
to his bloodthirsty hunger for power?

563
00:55:30,000 --> 00:55:32,640
Are we going to keep living
in fear like this?

564
00:55:32,720 --> 00:55:35,480
- No.
- No.

565
00:55:35,560 --> 00:55:36,560
Are you enduring this?

566
00:55:36,640 --> 00:55:40,240
- We won't!
- We won't!

567
00:55:40,320 --> 00:55:43,320
- We won't!
- You arrogant rebels.

568
00:55:45,320 --> 00:55:47,640
You dare stir the people

569
00:55:47,720 --> 00:55:50,320
against me.

570
00:55:50,400 --> 00:55:53,080
If you don't stop, you'll die.

571
00:55:53,160 --> 00:55:54,600
You're the one who has to stop.

572
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:56,240
Stop your corruption already, Kaipetch.

573
00:55:56,320 --> 00:55:57,960
You parasites dragging the land down.

574
00:55:58,040 --> 00:56:00,760
This country will fall
because of scum like you.

575
00:56:00,840 --> 00:56:02,800
- You bastard. Go to hell!
- You're evil!

576
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:06,800
- Evil!
- Damn you!

577
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:08,840
- Go to hell!
- You're evil!

578
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:11,640
- Go!
- Go to hell!

579
00:56:11,720 --> 00:56:15,360
Who's the one who deserves to die,
you lowborn peasant?

580
00:56:16,400 --> 00:56:20,320
<i>Om, phrakan deva.</i>
<i>I curse you into madness,</i>

581
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:23,160
<i>to writhe to death in fire and water.</i>

582
00:56:23,240 --> 00:56:25,960
<i>Om, phrakan deva sawaha sawahom.</i>

583
00:56:28,760 --> 00:56:31,640
Everyone, run! Run!

584
00:56:32,440 --> 00:56:33,640
Hey.

585
00:56:33,720 --> 00:56:36,600
Chang! Chang! Come out!

586
00:56:41,880 --> 00:56:42,720
Damn you.

587
00:56:44,360 --> 00:56:45,200
Let's go.

588
00:56:59,040 --> 00:57:00,560
Pae, Bandit Pud's nephew,

589
00:57:00,640 --> 00:57:04,000
gave a statement before he died
that you two were behind it.

590
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:14,360
Having no memories left at all

591
00:57:14,880 --> 00:57:16,520
might hurt less.

592
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:19,560
So that's why
you want to erase my memories.

593
00:57:19,640 --> 00:57:22,640
Tomorrow, I'll hold
the wrist-tying ceremony for you two.

594
00:57:22,720 --> 00:57:24,480
Isn't that too soon, Dad?

595
00:57:24,560 --> 00:57:26,880
You two have already
become husband and wife.

596
00:57:27,680 --> 00:57:28,920
What else is there to prepare?

597
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:21,920
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
